# LangGraph Agentic App for GitHub Issue Operations

A starter LangGraph-based multi-agent application scaffold derived from mined process artifacts in this workspace.

## Purpose

This app treats GitHub issue handling as an object-centric orchestration problem over:
- issues
- tasks
- commits
- users
- labels
- reviewers
- pull requests

It is grounded in the mined process roles:
- coordination-heavy: `issue_reporter`, `bot`
- execution-heavy: `contributor`, `feature_developer`, `maintainer`, `devops_engineer`, `quality_engineer`, `technical_writer`

## Current scope

This repository contains:
- a typed shared state model
- real GitHub REST integration for issue reads and issue mutations
- role prompts derived from mined role behaviors
- LangGraph node functions
- a top-level graph with conditional routing
- architecture documentation
- environment-based configuration loading

By default, write operations run in dry-run mode until configured otherwise.

